I started this account when I was 19 years old. I can’t even believe it has been that long. A lot has changed in the past 13 years. I have grown & changed in so many ways.

It’s been a long time since I’ve posted without feeling an underlying sense of anxiety. Without low key stressing over the fact that I feel like a much different person than I was when I initially started all of this.

It’s bizarre to even think about if I’m being honest. The pressure social media can put on us. But what it comes down to is that I love creating content. I love the feeling I get when I have an idea for a photo or a video. I love sharing with you & having this wonderful online community.

So here I am. After a 6 month break. Feeling like I’m starting new all over again. At 32 years old this time. Much older but overall just in a very different place in life🖤

I hope you’re ready for a bit of a life catch up over the next couple of weeks! We went on a couple of adventures I can’t wait to share with you + I have recommendations if you’re headed to Copenhagen anytime soon🫶🏻

🛳️After years of talking about it, we finally went on our first Disney cruise! We celebrated K’s 10th birthday & had such an incredible family adventure. Swipe for more candids of me & @theadamgregory 📷

We sailed out of San Diego since it was during the boys school & we didn’t want to take additional days off for travel. Very convenient option if you’re on the west coast!

We did a 5 night cruise that stopped off in Cabo & Baja. It was so warm & beautiful in Cabo + we went on a small boat/beach adventure where we saw whales! Such a magical experience![see last photo]🐋 

Highly recommend booking an off shore adventure through @disneycruiseline because this was genuinely the best booking I’ve ever done!

We stayed on the ship in Baja to have the amenities more to ourselves while others were off the ship & we were really happy with that decision because the kids clubs & pool were way less crowded.

Disney goes above & beyond with their cruises & we can’t recommend this one enough for a fun cruise adventure.

Now I’m just debating our next Disney adventure. Who knew they did other travel excursions called Adventures by Disney!? Thinking Europe next time!

Have you been on a Disney cruise or excursion? Would love to hear your thoughts in the comments for those who haven’t been before!

#disneycruise #disneycruiseline #disneycruiselife #adventuresbydisney

Starting my birthday week by finally posting about one of my absolute favorite cities in the world… COPENHAGEN🫶🏻🇩🇰

I first visited Copenhagen in 2018 on a girls trip & completely fell in love with this beautiful city. I couldn’t wait to go back with Adam & the boys so I’m thrilled we finally made this trip happen.

This is the street our hotel was located on😍 Every time we left to walk anywhere, I would just look around wondering if it was real life!

We stayed at Hotel SP34 (@brochnerhotels) & I’m going to do a full review asap but just a little preview on our thoughts… it was incredible! One of the best hotel stays I’ve EVER had & I’ll dive into all of the reasons why in my review soon so stay tuned for that this week!

🖤CURRENT FOCUS: Doing things that bring me pure joy🖤 *No beds were harmed in the making of this video*

I’ve been prioritizing happiness this year & even the smallest changes have made a huge impact. Seriously though, do the things that make you happy! Here are a few of my favorites:

•dancing anywhere & everywhere. Especially when I’m eating something yummy!

•swimming with my kids. I grew up swimming everyday in the summer & I love seeing my kids do the same

•the reflection of palm trees on mirrored buildings. So random but so prettyyy🌴

•reading a good book. Nothing puts me in a better mood then a good romcom!
